author: COMSOL
description: In this model, the acoustics of the Small Hall in the Konzerthaus Berlin is simulated with ray tracing. A full study of the room is performed in 1/3-octave bands with 10Â pairs of source-receiver positions. The room acoustic parameters are derived from the calculated impulse responses, and the results are compared with measurement data from a round robin study on room acoustic simulations.
